  "text": "Pharyngeal swabs were obtained from 19 patients with rubella-like illnesses. Sixteen were received from A. Flower (Public Health Laboratory, Leicester, United Kingdom) two were from soldiers at an army camp, and one was from a local patient. Blood samples were also collected, and rubella virus infection was confirmed by detection of rubella-specific immunoglobulin M by M antibody-capture radioimmunoassay [CITATION_1] . Patients referred to the Public Health Laboratory in Leicester were also tested for evidence of recent infection with parvovirus B19 and other viral causes of rash illness.",
